From: Prem Mallappa <pmallappa@caviumnetworks.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Oct 2013 15:40:07 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 324/382] EDAC: octeon_edac-lmc: Fixed crash for DIMM1-only case

Based on SDK octeon3_3.10.

Signed-off-by: Prem Mallappa <pmallappa@caviumnetworks.com>
Signed-off-by: David Daney <david.daney@cavium.com>
Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/edac/octeon_edac-lmc.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/edac/octeon_edac-lmc.c b/drivers/edac/octeon_edac-lmc.c
index fe88280..d3a6ac9 100644
--- a/drivers/edac/octeon_edac-lmc.c
+++ b/drivers/edac/octeon_edac-lmc.c
@@ -121,7 +121,7 @@ static int octeon_lmc_edac_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		if (!present)
 			return -ENXIO;
 
-		cfg0.u64 = cvmx_read_csr(CVMX_LMCX_MEM_CFG0(0));
+		cfg0.u64 = cvmx_read_csr(CVMX_LMCX_MEM_CFG0(mc));
 		if (!cfg0.s.ecc_ena) {
 			dev_info(&pdev->dev, "Disabled (ECC not enabled)\n");
 			return 0;
